modules.description: Provides functions for integrating AFL instrumentation with OCaml code, enabling fast fuzzing through compiled binaries. Operates on byte-code and native code representations, leveraging compiler flags for instrumentation. Used to test input validation and edge cases in critical code paths during security audits.

Provides a function to execute a given action repeatedly with persistent state, suitable for testing or monitoring. It operates on unit-returning functions and maintains internal state between calls. Used to run repeated checks or simulations without reinitializing resources.
